Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.41,0:00:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're no match for our martial arts skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.17,0:00:14.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, hand it over already...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.54,0:00:18.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...or else it'll get dirty with your blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.05,0:00:18.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.88,0:00:26.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought... I could defeat you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.73,0:00:31.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To tell you the truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.77,0:00:35.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Iceberg-san told me to run right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.90,0:00:42.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He told me to drop it quickly and run...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.74,0:00:45.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...since...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.45,0:00:48.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...it's a complete fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.12,0:00:55.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.88,0:01:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got stuck! Dammit! I got stuck again!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.42,0:01:02.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Why does this always happen?!\N--Straw Hat...!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.76,0:01:09.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tempest Kick.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.97,0:01:17.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His kicks cut the wall!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.57,0:01:20.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What the hell are these?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.94,0:01:23.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've got an emergency situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.15,0:01:25.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have time for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.20,0:01:33.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--I can't move!\N--Hey, restrain that guy, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.75,0:01:42.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go home!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.51,0:01:44.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got nothing I could give you people!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.43,0:01:51.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't, that puts us in quite a bind.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.89,0:01:56.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What should I tell you first...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.81,0:01:59.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...when you're about to die?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.65,0:02:03.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You disappointed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.15,0:02:04.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucci!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.70,0:02:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's your own fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.53,0:02:12.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should've given it to the\NGovernment when they asked nicely.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.41,0:02:13.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaku!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.50,0:02:20.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If possible, I wanted to make this town\Npart of my memory without hurting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.30,0:02:22.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kalifa...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.26,0:02:25.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you also inherited your\Nmaster's obstinacy, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.43,0:02:27.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blueno, from the bar...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.84,0:02:32.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guys... work for... the Government?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.93,0:02:38.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Going undercover\Nwas a pretty easy mission for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.98,0:02:44.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, your prudence\Nleaves me at a loss for words.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.90,0:02:47.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Iceberg-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.86,0:02:52.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where're the blueprints of\Nthe ancient weapon Pluton?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.66,0:03:00.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please tell us, before many people get hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.73,0:03:23.09,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right! Now let's move forward
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.11,0:03:26.59,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,with the sun always in our hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.61,0:03:29.93,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,As power passes through our clasped hands
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.95,0:03:37.95,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,let's grab hold of our wishes
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.92,0:03:48.57,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Working together, let's ride the giant waves
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.59,0:03:55.95,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hurry toward the excitement--\Nthere's the starting signal
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.97,0:04:02.88,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Now's the time to set sail-- let's raise anchor
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.90,0:04:09.97,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut through the rainbow-colored wind\Nand head for a sea of adventure
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.99,0:04:13.39,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be a journey fraught with injury
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.41,0:04:17.31,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,but what you cherish most will be right there
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.33,0:04:21.40,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,And if you get into a jam
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.42,0:04:24.40,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll always be there to protect you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.42,0:04:28.53,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right! Now let's move forward
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.55,0:04:32.16,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,with the sun always in our hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.18,0:04:35.12,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,If a storm hits, let's put\Nour arms around each other
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.14,0:04:39.41,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,and gaze at the light beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.43,0:04:43.38,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,If we gather up the pieces of our dreams
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.40,0:04:46.59,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,they'll make a map leading to tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.61,0:04:49.55,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,So let's grab hold of our wishes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.57,0:04:55.35,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,under the same flag-- together, we're one
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.37,0:05:03.37,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,One Piece
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.04,0:05:13.04,B1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(2000,2000)}"Secret Bond! Iceberg and Franky"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.31,0:05:32.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd better hurry up. The waves\Nand wind are getting rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.37,0:05:46.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's he doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.58,0:05:49.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,G-Give it back to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.75,0:05:57.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have to... have our ship repaired...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.51,0:06:01.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That money is crucial to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.47,0:06:05.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With that money...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.56,0:06:10.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...we can finally repair the Merry's scars!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.36,0:06:18.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't let you jerks have it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.07,0:06:19.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, he said\Nthat 200 million Berries
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.87,0:06:23.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was going to be used for\Nthe repair of their ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.12,0:06:27.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It appears that he doesn't know\NAqua Laguna is coming tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.04,0:06:32.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph! What a waste of effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.92,0:06:35.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! If I keep it airtight like this
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.68,0:06:39.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and reinforce the ship with lumber,\Nit'll probably do fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.35,0:06:42.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.47,0:06:45.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh... Who's there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.06,0:06:46.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Who's there"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.81,0:06:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey... You've already\Nforgotten me... long-nosed lad?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.19,0:06:55.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That voice... That guy's...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.45,0:06:57.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Wh-What'd you come\Nhere for, you bastard?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.57,0:07:00.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, don't lose your cool like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.12,0:07:04.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fighting in a place like this\Nwon't get us anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.00,0:07:07.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This area will soon sink due to a storm surge.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.00,0:07:13.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess we'll make this ship that you\Nlove so much our hostage, too, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.34,0:07:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What're you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.42,0:07:19.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... I have some business with Straw Hat...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.93,0:07:27.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...so I came here to kidnap you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.33,0:07:44.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. I used the back of my swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.95,0:07:47.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why'd you have to knock\Ndown all the shipwrights?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.62,0:07:49.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, Zoro is strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.83,0:07:52.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well... Let's go already!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.84,0:07:54.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Zoro! This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.25,0:07:55.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.30,0:07:56.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I said, this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.76,0:07:59.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could you go in the wrong direction\Nwhen we're leading the way for you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.63,0:08:00.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A miracle?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.26,0:08:01.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.68,0:08:04.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nami! Zoro has disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.39,0:08:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a miracle!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.02,0:08:14.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He got lost again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.62,0:08:25.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See?! My head came out...\Nsince it's made of rubber.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.28,0:08:29.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, good job! Get every body\Npart out by doing what you just did!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.08,0:08:37.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep! No problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.14,0:08:55.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right! I'm out... since I'm a rubber man!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.98,0:08:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good job! Okay! Take off my cuffs!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.36,0:09:02.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.95,0:09:10.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just wait and see... damn bull and skull...!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.33,0:09:16.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were undercover for five years.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.59,0:09:22.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't worry. We didn't\Ncut corners with our work.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.97,0:09:25.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do understand how dispirited you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.68,0:09:31.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, since we can't spend\Nany more time on this matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.81,0:09:36.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we're going to try our best to achieve our goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.11,0:09:42.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're thinking of putting up an\Nunwise resistance, I suggest you don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.57,0:09:45.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know the name "Cipher Pol," don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.91,0:09:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Government's\Nsupreme intelligence agency,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.79,0:09:54.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with eight bases around the world,\Ncalled CP1 through CP8 by people.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.37,0:09:59.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the Government orders it, they dig\Nup any kind of information in any place.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.09,0:10:01.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know about them...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.09,0:10:02.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...but only up to CP8.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.97,0:10:05.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.13,0:10:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, we are CP9, the 9th Cipher Pol,\Na supposedly non-existent unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.72,0:10:15.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since we possess a certain privilege,\Nwe can't reveal ourselves to the public.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.69,0:10:17.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Privilege?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.44,0:10:19.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.11,0:10:21.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is in the name of justice to the end,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.94,0:10:27.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but when there're citizens who are\Nuncooperative toward the Government...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.41,0:10:30.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...we have permission to kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.95,0:10:34.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How selfish...! Justice cannot\Nbe a reason for killing!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.96,0:10:39.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The World Government has\Npartially changed their thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.42,0:10:42.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rather than remaining in fear\Nof the weapon's restoration,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.51,0:10:44.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they decided to awaken it
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.67,0:10:50.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to make it into a force of justice\Nthat can end this Great Pirate Era.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.35,0:10:54.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, you don't want to help them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.10,0:10:59.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying that you don't want to "save"\Nthose people who keep being victimized
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.56,0:11:02.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by pirates around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.36,0:11:07.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nonsense... If the weapon is restored,\Nthe world will only fight over its power.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.28,0:11:10.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The damage only keeps growing!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.95,0:11:16.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that you don't trust\Nthe Government, Iceberg-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.87,0:11:24.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just know the nature of humans, that's all, lad.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.39,0:11:38.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Restrain yourself. Just how long are\Nyou going to keep acting like my boss?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.73,0:11:50.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaku, check his pulse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.11,0:11:58.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.21,0:12:00.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Iceberg-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.25,0:12:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To tell you the truth, we came up\Nwith a hypothesis a bit ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.67,0:12:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't worry. It's not that\Nwe're going to torture you now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.55,0:12:18.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All you have to do is listen to our\Nhypothesis without saying a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.85,0:12:26.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure your blood will tell us the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.72,0:12:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful when you walk. Or you'll get hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.26,0:12:57.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get off of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.31,0:13:01.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandma, Grandma! Aren't we going back yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.44,0:13:07.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... we've got a nice wind blowing.\NWhy don't we take the long way?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.11,0:13:11.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just perfect for sobering up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.03,0:13:15.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? When you're still drinking right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.32,0:13:20.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, can you sober up\Nwhile you're still drinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.29,0:13:25.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure I can. I haven't been drinking\Nfor several decades for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.04,0:13:32.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Er... Several decades?! That's weird!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.05,0:13:33.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's weird!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.97,0:13:37.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's weird! That's weird!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.26,0:13:40.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's weird!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.31,0:13:44.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah... it hasn't been several decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.48,0:13:52.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been eight years...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.82,0:14:01.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, I'll explain the thought\Nprocess leading to our hypothesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.00,0:14:08.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, we have doubts about your\Naction of passing off the fake to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.79,0:14:11.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You guessed that the culprits\Nwho came after the blueprints
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.26,0:14:15.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,were from the Government, so you\Nindicated where the fake was.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.93,0:14:21.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, if it happened to be\Nsomeone who had a grudge against you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.85,0:14:25.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and they just came to kill you,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.02,0:14:31.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the real blueprints would lose their owner\Nand they'd no longer be passed down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.15,0:14:35.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not stupid enough not\Nto think about that possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.36,0:14:37.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though you knew that,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.87,0:14:42.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you still didn't try to give the\Nreal blueprints to anyone tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.16,0:14:47.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means you've already\Nentrusted them with someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.08,0:14:52.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the very least,\Nyou don't have them with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.05,0:14:55.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So we think.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.72,0:14:59.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use. Don't act up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.05,0:15:01.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is still only a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.39,0:15:04.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, no convincing proof\Ncan be found anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.56,0:15:07.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The past five years of our\Nsurveillance and investigation
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.85,0:15:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,found no proof in your actions, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.02,0:15:14.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, the person who is\Nentrusted with the blueprints
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.40,0:15:21.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,has to have proper shipbuilding skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.62,0:15:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let me continue with our hypothesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.66,0:15:26.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now things are getting more interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.96,0:15:32.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These are the fake blueprints\Nthat you passed off on us earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.92,0:15:37.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I look at it carefully,\Nthere're signatures by the architects.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.09,0:15:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Tom," "Iceberg," and "Cutty Flam."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.64,0:15:43.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the end, there's a\Ncompany name: "Tom's Workers."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.76,0:15:49.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You might've thought that you outwitted\Nyour enemy by using these fakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.02,0:15:53.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you never even dreamed that\Nyour enemy was hiding this close.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.48,0:15:55.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was your miscalculation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.23,0:16:00.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To an overnight intruder\Nwho came after the blueprints,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.28,0:16:03.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,these would probably just be trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.24,0:16:07.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But to us, who lived in this\Ntown for the past five years,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.62,0:16:12.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,these architects' names are very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.08,0:16:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Iceberg-san, you have a guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.75,0:16:20.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom's Workers, led by the\Nlegendary shipwright Tom,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.59,0:16:23.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was a shipbuilding company\Nthat was full of mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.64,0:16:25.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it used to be on this island,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.76,0:16:28.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but there's no list of workers\Nor company registration.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.89,0:16:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just finding out the fact that you\Nwere Tom's disciple was quite hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.61,0:16:37.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to the report by the Government,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.94,0:16:40.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom had only two disciples.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.45,0:16:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And a Government official\Nverified that one of them died
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.99,0:16:46.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in an accident that happened eight years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.33,0:16:54.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know... that Tom's\Nviolent disciple Cutty Flam died?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.38,0:17:02.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, I remember hearing\Nthis name Cutty Flam before.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.38,0:17:08.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Iceberg-san, you have a guest. He said\Nyou'd know who if I told you "Cutty Flam."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.35,0:17:14.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was about four years ago, a little while\Nafter we started going undercover here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.31,0:17:19.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was a man who came through the\NGalley-La Company's gate to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.11,0:17:23.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He used that name just once.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.03,0:17:24.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I remember it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.20,0:17:27.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.53,0:17:29.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I show him in?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.75,0:17:37.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No... turn him away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.55,0:17:42.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.72,0:17:47.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Tom's other disciple Cutty Flam is still alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.68,0:17:54.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and lives in this town...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.94,0:18:01.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...after changing his name to Franky!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.69,0:18:09.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a roundabout way of meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.54,0:18:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're these?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.79,0:18:14.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, they're the blueprints\Nfor the ancient weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.41,0:18:16.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't use the name Cutty Flam from now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.75,0:18:18.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.92,0:18:22.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's only a matter of time before I get targeted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.92,0:18:26.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave the island with them... Franky.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.80,0:18:30.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like there's no mistake about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.31,0:18:35.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never thought that you and that\Nguy were connected like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.94,0:18:39.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that no matter\Nhow much we investigated,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.19,0:18:42.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we couldn't figure out his real identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.03,0:18:44.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But because he was a ship demolition worker
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.11,0:18:46.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and because of his behavior,\Nwe paid no attention to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.66,0:18:50.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see... Involving a dead person\Nwas indeed a perfect way to exploit
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.45,0:18:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,our blind spot, since our speculation\Nwas generated only from the facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.54,0:18:58.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Franky Family would come\Nto the shipyard to sell lumber.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.46,0:19:01.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So there were many chances\Nfor you to make an arrangement
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.46,0:19:03.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to give him the blueprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.38,0:19:05.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.05,0:19:09.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you could say that he was a\Nneighbor who kept a safe distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.30,0:19:12.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't have the blueprints with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.64,0:19:16.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it makes sense that you held firm.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.64,0:19:20.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it was your only fellow disciple\Nwhom you entrusted them with,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.65,0:19:25.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's also understandable that you didn't entrust\Nthem with any of the foremen at Galley-La.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.65,0:19:28.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, our speculations\Nare connected as one line.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.36,0:19:29.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In addition...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.82,0:19:37.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...your pounding blood proved it to be true!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.21,0:19:39.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Hurry!\N--Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.96,0:19:41.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you really sure this is the right way?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.21,0:19:45.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you say that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.38,0:19:50.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They've been hurt quite badly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.64,0:19:53.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over there! That door is the one!\NThere's no mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.18,0:19:59.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Many people are down over there, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.19,0:20:00.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.52,0:20:04.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, you go ahead! Ahead of us!\NCut down the door and make a dash!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.73,0:20:08.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Go ahead!\N--What the hell?! Don't order me around!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.86,0:20:14.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Straw Hat!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.16,0:20:20.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot! Wrong room! It's the next room!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.71,0:20:22.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the next room?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.33,0:20:26.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's not your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.09,0:20:28.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So many things are happening tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.67,0:20:33.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're only human. It's just natural that\Nyou couldn't hide your consternation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.51,0:20:36.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I appreciate what you've done for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.06,0:20:38.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're done with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.35,0:20:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hurry and find Franky.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.35,0:20:45.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You bastards...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.61,0:20:53.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.53,0:20:56.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Robin?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.29,0:21:00.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Luffy!\N--Luffy!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.83,0:21:08.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How bothersome...!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.26,0:21:15.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robin! I've finally found you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.85,0:21:19.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Luffy! Where the hell have you been?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.64,0:21:23.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robin! I'm glad that I could see you again!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.31,0:21:31.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on a sec... What's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.45,0:21:41.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, well, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.58,0:21:43.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Straw Hat...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.50,0:21:45.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Paulie...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.29,0:21:52.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Iceberg-san... What the hell...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.47,0:22:00.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.69,0:22:09.09,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,A piece of a dream that we started grasping
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.11,0:22:12.63,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Chasing after something constant
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.65,0:22:18.22,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We send our aspirations sailing into the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.24,0:22:20.52,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Even when we're exhausted
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.54,0:22:23.69,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We have a compass that can\Nsearch for something constant
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.71,0:22:29.11,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, do you think we can keep it forever?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.13,0:22:32.03,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,At the end of the dream\Nthat we will reach someday
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.05,0:22:34.99,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We want to be adults as we\Nare now as much as possible
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.01,0:22:37.78,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We pray to this endless sky that we look up at
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.80,0:22:40.87,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Eternally... Eternally...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.89,0:22:43.66,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Wild fantasies from our childhood
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.68,0:22:46.50,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We trace unforgettable memories
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.52,0:22:52.17,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,And try to keep the embers\Nburning that still consume us
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.19,0:22:55.01,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,To this familiar sunny sky
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.03,0:22:57.80,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Together we entrust our feelings
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.82,0:23:00.39,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We go beyond the changing time
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.41,0:23:08.41,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Eternally... Eternally...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.46,0:23:14.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Robin! Why are you with jerks like them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.46,0:23:18.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. They work for the\NGovernment, right?! So why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.26,0:23:19.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.43,0:23:22.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! I won't accept it! We're not done talking!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.47,0:23:26.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we are. I'll never see you guys again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.81,0:23:28.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next episode of One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.60,0:23:31.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Come Back, Robin! Showdown with CP9!"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.40,0:23:39.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
